-- Ogilvy & Mather, Scangroup of Kenya Secure All Approvals for Joint Venture
-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 2010-10-12T04:42:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/ogilvy-mather-scangroup-of-kenya-get-all-approvals-for-joint-venture.html
Scangroup Ltd., East Africa’s
biggest marketing and communications company, has received all
the approvals to enter into a partnership with Ogilvy and Mather
Worldwide to form Ogilvy Africa.  Scangroup acquired 51 percent of Ogilvy & Mather Africa BV
and 50 percent of Ogilvy East Africa Ltd., the company said in a
statement in the Nairobi-based Daily Nation.  “The transactions have been successfully completed and
accordingly, the board of directors of Scangroup on Oct. 8, 2010
issued a total of 13.88 million new ordinary shares,” the
statement said. The new shares began trading on the Nairobi
Stock Exchange yesterday, it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
